## Go further

### A. Classify roles with `CASE`

```sql
SELECT
    name,
    role,
    CASE
        WHEN role = 'admin' THEN 'Full access'
        WHEN role = 'editor' THEN 'Can edit content'
        WHEN role = 'viewer' THEN 'Read-only access'
        ELSE 'Unknown role'
    END AS access_level
FROM users;
```

### B. Compute totals for all products

```sql
SELECT
    product_name,
    item_price,
    quantity,
    item_price * quantity AS total_cost
FROM products;
```

### C. Filter rows like a conditional

```sql
SELECT name, age
FROM users
WHERE age >= 18;
```

